KATSINA – The Katsina State Government has assured local government council workers of continued support to ensure effective service delivery in the civil service. Alhaji Mustapha Muhammed Inuwa, the Secretary to the Government of the state, SGS, gave the assurance when he received the members of NULGE Katsina state branch during a courtesy visit in his office. Inuwa said Local Government staff deserve the desired support, as it is closer to the people at the grassroots. SMEs Gets Database In Katsina Masari Orders Reopening Of Filling Stations,   Cattle Markets In… Similarly, he added that the Local Government staff play a vital role in the transformation of the well-being of the people and charged them to discharge their duties with transparency. He however attributed the high cost of living, insecurity and drug abuse with lack of transparency and accountability in leadership to the problems in the local council. He also advised them to reciprocate the government gestures by reviving the attitude of discipline amongst the civil servants. Comrade Nasiru Wada Mai’Adua, the chairman of NULGE, earlier said the visit is to extend their gratitude for the support to the association especially, in the reviving of the local government staff salary scheme and grade level progression. He also acknowledged the Governor Masari led administration for its concern for the general well-being of its members at the local council level.